gle base mismatches or lesions this discovery has been a cornerstone for the development of dnabased electrochemical sensors awards and honorsedit barton was awarded the national medal of science by barack obama in  for discovery of a new property of the dna helix longrange electron transfer and for showing that electron transfer depends upon stacking of the base pairs and dna dynamics her experiments reveal a strategy for how dna repair proteins locate dna lesions and demonstrate a biological role for dnamediated charge transfer other awards include alan t waterman award of the national science foundation  first woman recipient fresenius award from phi lambda upsilon  first woman recipient eli lilly award in biological chemistry by the american chemical society  american chemical society award in pure chemistry  first woman recipient mayor of new yorks award in science and technology  american chemical society baekeland medal  first woman recipient fellow of the american academy of arts and sciences  macarthur foundation fellowship  garvan medal of the american chemical society  tolman award of the american chemical society  first woman recipient havinga medal  paul karrer gold medal  first woman recipient nichols medal of the american chemical society  first woman recipient weizmann women  science award  elected american philosophical society  elected national academy of sciences  ronald breslow award in biomimetic chemistry from the american chemical society  acs gibbs medal  fa cotton medal for excellence in chemical research of the american chemical society  national medal of science  fellow of the american chemical society acs  american institute of chemists gold medal  priestley medal  referencesedit  odom duncan t  the application of metallointercalators in recognition of and charge trasnport in nucleic acids caltechedu phd thesis california institute of technology oclc    a b c d e f g h i barton jacqueline k march   a career in chemistry chemical  engineer