ince been acquired by bd diagnostics barton has taught more than  graduate and postdoctoral students many of whom are women recognized as a superb role model not just for young women but for all young scientists barton advises others that the best thing that i can do for women in science is first to do good science she became the arthur and marian hanisch memorial professor of chemistry in  she was named chair of the division of chemistry and chemical engineering of california institute of technology effective july   barton has been a member of the board of dow chemical since  she has also served on the gilead sciences scientific advisory board  in  she married peter dervan a fellow chemist and professor at caltech who is also a national medal of science winner she has two children a daughter elizabeth and a stepson andrew research summaryedit barton third right receiving the national medal of science at the white house in  barton introduced the application of transition metal complexes to probe recognition and reactions of double helical dna she has designed chiral metal complexes which mimic the properties of dnabinding proteins allowing other researchers the capability to simulate and analyze experiments in this nature barton additionally established that dna charge transport chemistry is extremely sensitive to intervening perturbations in the dna base stack as with single base mismatches or lesions this discovery has been a cornerstone for the development of dnabased electrochemical sensors awards and honorsedit barton was awarded the national medal of science by barack obama in  for discovery of a new property of the dna helix longrange electron transfer and for showing that electron transfer depends upon stacking of the base pairs and dna dynamics her experiments reveal a strategy for how dna repair proteins locate dna lesions and demonstrate a biological role for dnamediated charge transfer other awards include alan t waterman award of the national science foundation  first woman recipient fresenius award from phi lambda upsilon  first woman recipient eli lilly award in biological chemistry by the american chemical society  american chemical society award in pure chemistry  first woman recipient mayor of new yorks award in science and technology  american chemical society baekeland medal  first woman recipient fellow of the american academy of arts and sciences  macarthur foundation fellowship  garvan medal of the american chemical society  tolman award of the american chemical society  first woman recipient havinga medal  paul karrer gold medal  first woman recipient nichols medal of the american chemical society  first woman recipient weizmann women  science award  elected american philosophical society  elected national academy of sciences  ronald breslow award in biomimetic chemistry from the american chemical society  acs gibbs medal  fa cotton medal for excellence in chemical research of the american chemical society  national medal of science  fellow of the american chemical society acs  american institute of chemists gold medal  priestley medal  referencesedit  odom duncan t  the application of metallointercalators in recognition of and charge trasnport in nucleic acids caltechedu phd thesis california institute of technology oclc    a b c d e f g h i barton jacqueline k march   a career in chemistry chemical  engineering news   – retrieved  april    bernice segal  a professor of chemistry the new york times april   retrieved  april    a b c d e f g h i j ghaffari elizabeth  women leaders at work untold tales of women achieving their ambitions apress pp – isbn    the robert a welch foundation research bulletin houston texas robert a welch foundation   thompson clifford  current biography yearbook  th annual cumulation ed new york h w wilson p  isbn    jacqueline barton phd ’ and michael l lomax ma ’ to receive distinguished achievement awards at gsas convocation ceremonies graduate school of arts and sciences of